4. The Perception Layer: Neural Cluster Decoupler (NCD)

4.1 Synthetic Sensor & Noise Generation

Â· Process: The physics simulator generates a ground-truth state S_true. A sensor model adds Gaussian noise ð’©(Î¼, Ïƒ) to performance parameters (e.g., p_c Â± 2 bar).
Â· Acoustic Emission (AE) Synthesis: AE_raw(t) = FFT^{-1}[ Î£_Cluster_Noise + Spallation_Event(Î´_TBC) ]. Status: ðŸ¤– (ML Model). Noise profile includes broadband roar and turbopump harmonics.

4.2 Temporal Fusion Transformer (TFT) Architecture

Â· Purpose: A denoising autoencoder that maps 33 channels of AE_raw(t) to a clean signal for a target engine.
Â· Input: (batch, 33, time_seq). Includes spatial embedding for engine position.
Â· Core: Multi-head self-attention layers followed by convolutional decoder.
Â· Output: Residual Anomaly Energy E_res(t). Status: ðŸ¤–. Trained entirely on synthetic data pairs (AE_raw, clean_event).

4.3 MISO Delay-and-Sum Beamformer

Â· Process: Time-aligns signals based on known engine geometry and sound speed in structure (v_s â‰ˆ 5000 m/s): y_target(t) = Î£_j w_j * x_j(t + Ï„_ij).
Â· Status: ðŸŸ¡. Physics is sound (ðŸ”µ), but effectiveness depends on accurate modeling of wave propagation in the monolithic block, which is complex (ðŸŸ¡).

