5. The Intelligence Layer: POMDP Control Core

5.1 Formal POMDP Definition (S, A, O, T, Î©, R, Î³)

Â· States S: Hidden degradation states (e.g., [Î´_TBC, x_ox, Ï‰_fatigue]).
Â· Actions A: Continuous vector [throttle, Î”O/F, ITC_power, coolant_override].
Â· Observations O: Noisy sensor outputs O_sim(t), including E_res from NCD.
Â· Transition Model T(s'|s,a): Defined by the physics models in Sections 2 & 3. This is the simulator's internal truth. Status: ðŸŸ¡/ðŸ”´. Credibility depends on constituent models.
Â· Observation Model Î©(o|s',a): A learned neural network. Estimates probability of sensor reading o given true state s'. Status: ðŸ¤–. Trained on millions of (S_true, O_sim) pairs from the simulator.
Â· Reward R(s,a): R = w1*R_perf + w2*R_health + w3*R_mission - w4*R_penalty. Includes exponential penalty for high p_O2 and T_wall.

5.2 Belief State & The Bayesian Filter

The controller maintains a probability distribution b_t(s) over hidden states, updated via:
b_{t+1}(s') âˆ Î©(o_{t+1} | s', a_t) â€¢ Î£_s T(s' | s, a_t) â€¢ b_t(s)
This fuses the NCD's anomaly detection with model-based predictions.

5.3 Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL)

Â· Setup: 33 parallel instances of the simulator, coupled acoustically and thermally via view factors F_ij.
Â· Architecture: Centralized Training, Decentralized Execution (CTDE). A global critic learns cooperative strategies; each engine runs a local actor Ï€_i(a_i | o_i, b_i(s)).
Â· Differentiated Policies: Inner-ring engines weight R_health more; outer-ring engines weight R_perf more to compensate.
Â· The "Firebreak" Protocol: A hard-coded sequence triggered by a high-confidence breach belief (P(S_4) > 0.8) to isolate a failing engine and shield its neighbors.

