7. Path to De-Risking & Physical Reality

7.1 Critical Path: Transitioning ðŸ”´ to ðŸŸ¡

The single most important action is executing the High-Pressure Oxidation DOE:

1. Objective: Empirically determine m and Q_l at p_O2 = 100-400 bar, T = 900-1300 K.
2. Outcome: Replace literature extrapolations with fitted constants and uncertainty bounds.
3. Ripple Effect: Recalibrates the Transition Model T(s'|s,a), the Observation Model Î©, and requires retraining the POMDP policy. This work transitions the largest ðŸ”´ to a quantified ðŸŸ¡.

7.2 The "Iron Bird" Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL) Phase

Â· Purpose: Test the AI stack against real-world latency using actual flight computers and actuators connected to the real-time simulator.
Â· Key Test: "Time-to-Truth" must be < 150ms for the control loop (sensor â†’ NCD â†’ POMDP â†’ actuator command).
Â· Success Criterion: 99.9% mission success rate in HIL with fault injection.

7.3 Final Implementation Roadmap

1. Complete DOE & Model Recalibration. (Transition ðŸ”´â†’ðŸŸ¡)
