---

8. Conclusion: The Blueprint as a Falsifiable Hypothesis

The NCP-X Final Blueprint is not a construction document. It is a detailed, uncertainty-quantified proposal for a computational experiment. Its value lies in providing a complete, self-consistent framework to test a revolutionary approach to engine control. The explicit labeling of ðŸ”´ðŸŸ¡ðŸ”µ forces rigorous confrontation with knowledge gaps and directs research resources to where they are most needed: empirically resolving the high-pressure oxidation frontier.

By following this plan, the outcome will be unambiguous: either the autonomous framework demonstrably achieves its reliability target in high-fidelity simulation, justifying a massive investment in physical development, or it reveals fundamental flaws in the concept, saving equal resources. This is the essence of simulation-first design.

